<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<title>Fairness Report: {{ r.system_id }}</title>
<style>
  body { font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; color: #1a1a1a;
         line-height: 1.5; max-width: 1000px; margin: 24px auto; padding: 0 16px; }
  h1 { color: #0b3d63; margin-bottom: 2px; }
  h2 { color: #0b3d63; border-bottom: 1px solid #d0d7de; padding-bottom: 4px; margin-top: 28px; }
  .muted { color: #666; }
  table { border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; margin: 8px 0 16px; font-size: 13px; }
  th, td { border: 1px solid #d0d7de; padding: 6px 10px; text-align: left; }
  th { background: #f6f8fa; }
  .assess { background: #f0f4f8; border: 1px solid #d0d7de; border-radius: 4px;
            padding: 10px 14px; margin: 10px 0; }
  .sev-critical { color: #c62828; font-weight: bold; }
  .sev-warning { color: #b58a00; font-weight: bold; }
  code { background: #f6f8fa; padding: 1px 4px; border-radius: 3px; }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<h1>AI Fairness &amp; Bias Report</h1>
<p class="muted">System <code>{{ r.system_id }}</code> · evaluated {{ r.evaluation_date }}
   · population {{ r.population_size }} · {{ r.slices_evaluated|length }} slices</p>

<div class="assess"><strong>Overall assessment:</strong> {{ r.overall_assessment }}</div>

<h2>Disparities flagged</h2>
{% if r.disparities_flagged %}
<table>
  <tr><th>Slice</th><th>Metric</th><th>Groups (low → high)</th><th>Magnitude</th><th>95% CI</th><th>Severity</th></tr>
  {% for f in r.disparities_flagged %}
  <tr>
    <td>{{ f.slice_name }}</td>
    <td>{{ f.metric }}</td>
    <td>{{ f.disparate_groups | join(" → ") }}</td>
    <td>{{ "%.3f"|format(f.magnitude) }}</td>
    <td>[{{ "%.3f"|format(f.confidence_interval[0]) }}, {{ "%.3f"|format(f.confidence_interval[1]) }}]</td>
    <td class="sev-{{ f.severity }}">{{ badge[f.severity] }}</td>
  </tr>
  {% endfor %}
</table>
<p class="muted">Thresholds: warning if |magnitude| &gt; 0.05, critical if &gt; 0.10.</p>
{% else %}
<p>No disparities above the warning threshold.</p>
{% endif %}

<h2>Metrics by slice</h2>
{% for slice_name, metrics in r.metrics_by_slice.items() %}
<h3>{{ slice_name }}</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>Metric</th><th>Disparity magnitude (max − min)</th></tr>
  {% for metric, value in metrics.items() %}
  <tr><td>{{ metric }}</td><td>{{ "%.4f"|format(value) }}</td></tr>
  {% endfor %}
</table>
{% endfor %}

{% if roc_div or reliability_div %}
<h2>Diagnostics by group</h2>
{{ reliability_div | safe }}
{{ roc_div | safe }}
{% endif %}

<h2>Plain-language summary</h2>
<p>
This report compares how the model performs for different groups of patients. A
"disparity magnitude" is the gap between the best- and worst-served group for a
given measure — larger gaps mean the model treats some groups less well than
others. {{ r.overall_assessment }}
</p>
<p class="muted">
Demographic parity compares how often each group receives a positive prediction.
Equal opportunity compares the true-positive rate (catching real cases). Equalized
odds also considers false alarms. PPV parity compares how often a positive
prediction is correct. Calibration (Brier score) measures whether predicted
probabilities match observed outcomes.
</p>
</body>
</html>
